{"id":721842122,"lang":"java","time":"2Â months","timestamp":1655187690,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"16 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/721842122/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Delete Operation for Two Strings","memory":"47.4 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {\n        int m =word1.length();\n        int n =word2.length();\n        int[][] dp = new int[m+1][n+1];\n        for(int i=0;i<=m;i++){\n            for(int j=0;j<=n;j++){\n                if(i==0 || j==0)    continue;\n                if(word1.charAt(i-1)==word2.charAt(j-1))    dp[i][j] = 1+ dp[i-1][j-1];\n                else    dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i-1][j] , dp[i][j-1]);\n            }\n        }\n        //return dp[m][n];\n        return m+n - 2*dp[m][n];\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"delete-operation-for-two-strings"}
